<item>
            <title>[WFLY-3295] AsyncContext#start runs in caller thread</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-3295</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;javax.servlet.AsyncContext.start(Runnable)&lt;/tt&gt; seems to run the runnable in the caller thread. In order for this method to be useful it should be run in a different thread.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll attach a class to demonstrate the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
